800a42\" class=\"AppleTopic apd-topic dark-mode-enabled\" data-istaskopen=\"true\" data-designversion=\"2\" lang=\"en\"><a name=\"mchl4f800a42\"></a><figure class=\"topicIcon\"><img src=\"https://help.apple.com/assets/63BCA927AAE78C58DD7FBE35/63BCA92EAAE78C58DD7FBE76/en_US/058e4af8e726290f491044219d2eee73.png\" alt=\"\" height=\"30\" width=\"30\" originalImageName=\"SharedGlobalArt/AppIconTopic_Finder.png\"></figure><h1>Unlock your Mac and approve requests with Apple Watch</h1><p>When you’re wearing your Apple Watch and are near your Mac, you can use your Apple Watch to unlock your Mac or approve app requests, without having to enter a password.</p><figure><img src=\"https://help.apple.com/assets/63BCA927AAE78C58DD7FBE35/63BCA92EAAE78C58DD7FBE76/en_US/279901fee61b6ddd7f8758a8a27ed984.png\" alt=\"The Auto Unlock screen with a message in the center of the screen that says the Mac is being unlocked with Apple Watch.\" height=\"290\" width=\"466\" originalImageName=\"Art/S0970_AutoUnlock.png\"></figure><div class=\"Alert\"><p class=\"Note\"><em>Note: </em>To use these features, make sure you’re wearing your unlocked Apple Watch with your Mac nearby, you’re <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=sign-in-with-your-apple-id&amp;version=13.0&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=GLOS0159E54B&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=13.0&amp;aside=true\" class=\"xRef Aside\">signed in with the same Apple ID</a> on your Mac (a mid-2013 or later model) and Apple Watch, and <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=two-factor-authentication&amp;version=13.0&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=GLOS57B6C063&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=13.0&amp;aside=true\" class=\"xRef Aside\">two-factor authentication</a> is turned on for your Apple ID.</p></div><div id=\"mchl3cf1f8cb\" class=\"Task\"><h2 aria-controls=\"aria-mchl3cf1f8cb\" class=\"Name\">Turn on Auto Unlock and Approve with Apple Watch</h2><div class=\"TaskBody\" role=\"region\" aria-hidden=\"false\" id=\"aria-mchl3cf1f8cb\"><ol><li><p>Choose Apple menu <picture><source media=\"(not all)\" srcset=\"https://help.apple.com/assets/63BCA927AAE78C58DD7FBE35/63BCA92EAAE78C58DD7FBE76/en_US/0e2c53fa5a413cc7ff5099226fb50188.png\" originalImageName=\"SharedGlobalArt/IL_AppleLogo_11~dark.png\"></source><img src=\"https://help.apple.com/assets/63BCA927AAE78C58DD7FBE35/63BCA92EAAE78C58DD7FBE76/en_US/2f77cc85238452e25cb517130188bf99.png\" alt=\"\" height=\"30\" width=\"24\" originalImageName=\"SharedGlobalArt/IL_AppleLogo_11.png\"></picture> &gt; System Settings, then click Touch ID &amp; Password <img src=\"https://help.apple.com/assets/63BCA927AAE78C58DD7FBE35/63BCA92EAAE78C58DD7FBE76/en_US/bafd555c29d06d38658a8964d20b2517.png\" alt=\"\" height=\"30\" width=\"30\" originalImageName=\"SharedGlobalArt/AppIconTopic_TouchID.png\"> in the sidebar. (You may need to scroll down.)</p><p><a href=\"x-help-action://openPrefPane?bundleId=com.apple.Touch-ID-Settings.extension*TouchIDPasswordPrefs\" class=\"URL\">Open Touch ID &amp; Password settings for me</a></p></li><li><p>Go to Apple Watch on the right, then turn on the option next to the name of your watch.</p><p>This option is only available if your Apple Watch has watchOS 6 or later installed.</p></li></ol></div></div><div id=\"mchl5101a417\" class=\"Task\"><h2 aria-controls=\"aria-mchl5101a417\" class=\"Name\">Unlock your Mac</h2><div class=\"TaskBody\" role=\"region\" aria-hidden=\"false\" id=\"aria-mchl5101a417\"><p>Wake your Mac from its idle state by pressing any keyboard key or, on a Mac laptop, by opening the display. The screen indicates that your Mac is being unlocked.</p></div></div><div id=\"mchl705cc12b\" class=\"Task\"><h2 aria-controls=\"aria-mchl705cc12b\" class=\"Name\">Approve app requests</h2><div class=\"TaskBody\" role=\"region\" aria-hidden=\"false\" id=\"aria-mchl705cc12b\"><p>When an app requires authentication on your Mac—for example, to view passwords, unlock notes or settings, and approve app installations—an approval request from your Mac appears on your Apple Watch.</p><p>Double-click the side button of your Apple Watch to approve the task request.</p></div></div><p>If you’re not sure if your Mac supports Auto Unlock and Approve with Apple Watch, choose Apple menu <picture><source media=\"(not all)\" srcset=\"https://help.apple.com/assets/63BCA927AAE78C58DD7FBE35/63BCA92EAAE78C58DD7FBE76/en_US/0e2c53fa5a413cc7ff5099226fb50188.png\" originalImageName=\"SharedGlobalArt/IL_AppleLogo_11~dark.png\"></source><img src=\"https://help.apple.com/assets/63BCA927AAE78C58DD7FBE35/63BCA92EAAE78C58DD7FBE76/en_US/2f77cc85238452e25cb517130188bf99.png\" alt=\"\" height=\"30\" width=\"24\" originalImageName=\"SharedGlobalArt/IL_AppleLogo_11.png\"></picture> &gt; About This Mac, click More Info, then click System Report at the bottom of the window. In the sidebar, in the Network section, click Wi-Fi, then look on the right for “Auto Unlock: Supported.”</p><p>If you’re the administrator for another user on your Mac, you can log in to their user account and turn on Auto Unlock or Approve with Apple Watch for them, as long as their Apple ID uses two-factor authentication and their Apple Watch has the required version of watchOS installed.</p><div class=\"LinkUniversal\"><strong>See also</strong><a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=set-up-icloud-on-your-mac&amp;version=13.0&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MH36834&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=13.0\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">Set up iCloud features on Mac</a><a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=work-across-devices-using-continuity&amp;version=13.0&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHL1D734309&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=13.0\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">Use Continuity to work across Apple devices</a><a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=change-the-login-password-on-mac&amp;version=13.0&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHLP1550&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=13.0\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">Change the login password on Mac</a></div></body>","tags":[{"type":"audience","refKey":"PUBLIC_USERS","tagPath":"audience/PUBLIC_USERS","title":"Public"}]}]},"categoryInfo":{"categories":["IP-Meta/DesignVersion/DesignVersion2","platform/mac","DisplayVersion/macOS Ventura 13","MetaFollow/MetaFollowOFF","ContentMode/liveContent","SupportSearchIndex/SupportSearchIndexON","ArchivalStatus/Archived","ExternalIndex/ExternalIndexOFF"],"categoryDictionaries":[{"key":"SupportSearchIndexON","name":"SupportSearchIndexON","englishName":"SupportSearchIndexON","displayName":"SupportSearchIndexON","articleCount":"120736"},{"key":"liveContent","name":"Live Content","englishName":"Live Content","displayName":"Live Content","articleCount":"135880"},{"key":"IP-Meta","name":"IP-Meta","englishName":"IP-Meta","displayName":"IP-Meta","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"ContentMode","name":"ContentMode","englishName":"ContentMode","displayName":"ContentMode","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"DesignVersion2","name":"DesignVersion 2","englishName":"DesignVersion 2","displayName":"DesignVersion 2","articleCount":"135315"},{"key":"MetaFollow","name":"MetaFollow","englishName":"MetaFollow","displayName":"MetaFollow","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"ExternalIndex","name":"ExternalIndex","englishName":"ExternalIndex","displayName":"ExternalIndex","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"DesignVersion","name":"DesignVersion","englishName":"DesignVersion","displayName":"DesignVersion","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"platform","name":"platform","englishName":"platform","displayName":"platform","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"mac","name":"mac","englishName":"mac","displayName":"mac","articleCount":"85819"},{"key":"Archived","name":"Archived","englishName":"Archived","displayName":"Archived","articleCount":"124678"},{"key":"ArchivalStatus","name":"ArchivalStatus",